This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video processing and image enhancement techniques. The use of deep learning models also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for temporal super-resolution, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the recurrence of small space-time patches, which could be relevant to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
